comments: Capela (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Cunningham's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact.
Cunningham (DET) extends his arm into Young's (ATL) path and initiates contact with Young's front during the drive.

Replay review of the foul called on Hayes (DET) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Hayes makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Young (ATL) as Young rips through.
Hayes (DET) places his hand momentarily on Collins' (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as they roll into the lane.
Capela (ATL) firms up in his screening position in Livers' (DET) path and absorbs the contact along the baseline. Additionally, Capela remains in bounds as the contact occurs during the screen.

Capela (ATL) maintains a rested hand on Cunningham's (DET) side and marginal contact occurs as Cunningham fades away from the basket during the driving shot attempt.
Bogdanovic (ATL) and Bagley III (DET) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.

The play originates inside the LDB.  Bogdanovic (ATL), the primary defender on the play, jumps vertically while inside the RA and collapses his arm to his chest as he absorbs the contact from Cunningham (DET).
Cunningham (DET) brings his arm down and makes contact with Hunter's (ATL) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Bagley III (DET) is already in Collins' (ATL) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact.
Bogdanovic (ATL) places his hand momentarily on Bagley III's (DET) side before immediately removing his hand.

Cunningham (DET) rests his hand on Collins' (ATL) back and marginal contact occurs as Cunningham releases away to pursue the rebound.

Bogdanovic (ATL) wraps Cunningham's (DET) midsection, affecting Cunningham's FOM and subsequently allowing Bogdanovic to make contact with the ball.
Bagley III (DET) jumps forward into Collins' (ATL) body and delivers contact as Collins elevates to retrieve the pass.
Young (ATL) legally contests Cunningham's (DET) jump shot attempt.

Bagley III (DET) and Capela (ATL) briefly engage and disengage as the pick is set.
Bagley III (DET) extends his left hand into Young's (ATL) path and initiates contact with Young's front prior to Young's gather.  The play should have been deemed a non-shooting foul.
Joseph (DET) establishes a screening position outside of Collins' (ATL) field of view, and he gives Collins a step to avoid the contact.
Capela (ATL) cleanly blocks Cunningham's (DET) driving shot attempt.
Young (ATL) and Joseph (DET) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Joseph (DET) is turning away from Young (ATL) as marginal body contact occurs prior to the start of Young's upward shooting motion.
Joseph (DET) contests Young's (ATL) shot near the rim and marginal contact occurs after the release of the shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) makes contact with the ball while it is outside the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Grant (DET) cleanly deflects the ball away from Capela (ATL) during rebounding.  Any ensuing contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
